1568
1:46:40,326 --> 1:46:42,429
EVERYONE.


1569
1:46:42,429 --> 1:46:45,665
Goldhagen, voice-over:
I HAD BEEN WORKING
ON "WORSE THAN WAR"


1570
1:46:45,665 --> 1:46:50,603
FOR ABOUT 10 YEARS BEFORE
THE FILM PROJECT BEGAN.


1571
1:46:50,603 --> 1:46:52,906
WHEN I WRITE A BOOK,
I CAN PRETTY MUCH SAY
WHATEVER I WANT TO,


1572
1:46:52,906 --> 1:46:55,575
AND IF I DECIDE SOMETHING
NEEDS 20 PAGES OF ELABORATION,


1573
1:46:55,575 --> 1:46:56,776
THEN I DO IT.


1574
1:46:56,776 --> 1:46:58,278
EVEN THOUGH I HAD THOUGHT
AT THE BEGINNING,


1575
1:46:58,278 --> 1:47:1,181
"WELL, I KNOW WHAT
THIS FILM SHOULD SAY,"


1576
1:47:1,181 --> 1:47:2,615
IT TURNED INTO SOMETHING
QUITE DIFFERENT


1577
1:47:2,615 --> 1:47:4,284
AND INFINITELY BETTER
THAN ANYTHING


1578
1:47:4,284 --> 1:47:8,221
I WOULD HAVE PRODUCED
HAD I BEEN THE FILMMAKER


1579
1:47:8,221 --> 1:47:11,24
BECAUSE I PROBABLY WOULD HAVE
PRODUCED A NICE TWO-HOUR LECTURE


1580
1:47:11,24 --> 1:47:12,826
OF SOME KIND WITH VISUALS


1581
1:47:12,826 --> 1:47:15,962
INSTEAD OF A FILM THAT IS
VISUALLY ARRESTING


1582
1:47:15,962 --> 1:47:17,73
AND EMOTIONALLY EVOCATIVE


1583
1:47:17,73 --> 1:47:21,101
AND, AS POWERFUL AS THE BOOK IS,


1584
1:47:21,101 --> 1:47:26,206
IN SOME WAYS
OBVIOUSLY MORE POWERFUL.


1585
1:47:26,206 --> 1:47:31,77
WHEN MY FATHER AND I WENT
TO WHERE HE HAD LIVED
DURING THE HOLOCAUST,


1586
1:47:31,77 --> 1:47:35,915
SARAH MY WIFE
AND GIDEON OUR SON CAME WITH US.


1587
1:47:35,915 --> 1:47:38,685
GIDEON AT THE TIME
WAS 7 YEARS OLD,


1588
1:47:38,685 --> 1:47:40,386
AND HE WAS DEEPLY INTERESTED.


1589
1:47:40,386 --> 1:47:42,522
HE'S VERY CLOSE MY PARENTS.
THEY LIVE NEARBY.


1590
1:47:42,522 --> 1:47:45,625
HE WAS DEEPLY INTERESTED IN
GOING TO WHERE GRANDPA WAS FROM.


1591
1:47:45,625 --> 1:47:47,26
SO THEY CAME
ON THE TRIP WITH US,


1592
1:47:47,26 --> 1:47:51,931
AND IT WAS SOMETHING THAT MADE
MY FATHER ENORMOUSLY HAPPY.


1593
1:47:51,931 --> 1:47:54,434
THAT ONE OF HIS GRANDCHILDREN
COULD SEE WHERE


1594
1:47:54,434 --> 1:47:57,17
MY FATHER CAME FROM
AND WHERE HE SUFFERED


1595
1:47:57,17 --> 1:47:58,838
AND WHERE HIS FAMILY SUFFERED


1596
1:47:58,838 --> 1:48:1,674
MADE THE TRIP,
IF ONE CAN SAY SUCH A THING,


1597
1:48:1,674 --> 1:48:12,719
TWICE AS MOVING AND MEMORABLE
AND MEANINGFUL FOR HIM.


1598
1:48:12,719 --> 1:48:15,155
THERE'S NO DOUBT THAT
MY FATHER INFLUENCED


1599
1:48:15,155 --> 1:48:19,125
MY INITIAL DIRECTION
OF WORKING ON THE HOLOCAUST,


1600
1:48:19,125 --> 1:48:20,827
BUT IT'S LESS BECAUSE
HE WAS A SURVIVOR


1601
1:48:20,827 --> 1:48:23,429
THAN HE WAS A PROFESSOR
WHO STUDIED THIS,


1602
1:48:23,429 --> 1:48:25,632
AND I GREW UP
WITH THIS MATERIAL IN MY HOME


1603
1:48:25,632 --> 1:48:28,501
ALWAYS WITH THE PURPOSE
NOT OF TELLING A TALE OF WOE,


1604
1:48:28,501 --> 1:48:31,538
WHICH IT IS,
BUT OF UNDERSTANDING
AND EXPLAINING.


1605
1:48:31,538 --> 1:48:35,775
THIS WAS ALWAYS MY ORIENTATION
FROM THE TIME I CAN REMEMBER


1606
1:48:35,775 --> 1:48:40,113
KNOWING OR THINKING ABOUT IT
OR DISCUSSING IT,


1607
1:48:40,113 --> 1:48:47,22
BUT IT CHANGES YOU
TO SEE THE PLACES.


1608
1:48:47,22 --> 1:48:51,624
THE CLICHÉ "A PICTURE'S
WORTH A THOUSAND WORDS"


1609
1:48:51,624 --> 1:48:55,695
ONLY BEGINS TO CONVEY
WHAT BEING IN A PLACE


1610
1:48:55,695 --> 1:48:57,864
AND SITTING
ACROSS FROM THE VICTIMS


1611
1:48:57,864 --> 1:49:1,334
AND SEEING THE LOCATIONS
WHERE PEOPLE WERE SLAUGHTERED


1612
1:49:1,334 --> 1:49:5,71
AND BEING IN A FORENSIC LAB
WITH THE REMAINS OF VICTIMS


1613
1:49:5,71 --> 1:49:7,173
OR BEING IN A MASS GRAVE


1614
1:49:7,173 --> 1:49:10,143
OR STANDING ACROSS
FROM A MASTERMIND OF GENOCIDE


1615
1:49:10,143 --> 1:49:12,912
SUCH AS RÍOS MONTT.


1616
1:49:12,912 --> 1:49:14,647
IT CHANGES YOU.


1617
1:49:14,647 --> 1:49:17,417
IT IS MORE THAN WORTH
A THOUSAND WORDS.


1618
1:49:17,417 --> 1:49:23,556
IT'S WORTH ENDLESS,
ENDLESS VOLUMES OF WORDS.


1619
1:49:23,556 --> 1:49:28,394
IN RWANDA, WE GAINED ACCESS
TO ONE OF THE PRISON CAMPS.


1620
1:49:28,394 --> 1:49:33,266
IT'S ACTUALLY A WORK CAMP
FOR PRISONERS WHO CONFESSED


1621
1:49:33,266 --> 1:49:35,335
TO THEIR CRIMES,
OR AT LEAST SOME CRIMES,


1622
1:49:35,335 --> 1:49:38,705
TO CONFESS TO HAVING
PARTICIPATED IN THE GENOCIDE.


1623
1:49:38,705 --> 1:49:41,507
IF YOU CAN BELIEVE THAT,
THERE ARE ABOUT 1,000 PEOPLE
IN THIS PRISON.


1624
1:49:41,507 --> 1:49:43,376
THERE WERE NO GUARDS.


1625
1:49:43,376 --> 1:49:45,78
SO WE INTERVIEWED
THE PERPETRATORS IN THE FIELD.


1626
1:49:45,78 --> 1:49:46,479
THE WARDEN JUST BROUGHT
PEOPLE TO US.


1627
1:49:46,479 --> 1:49:49,15
WE HAD NO IDEA
WHO WE'D BE TALKING TO,


1628
1:49:49,15 --> 1:49:50,75
AND ALSO, WE WALKED AMONG THEM.


1629
1:49:50,75 --> 1:49:57,257
THEY WERE TILLING
THE GROUND WITH HOES
AND PICKS AND MACHETES,


1630
1:49:57,257 --> 1:50:0,159
CLEARING IT,
AND YOU'RE WALKING AMONG THEM


1631
1:50:0,159 --> 1:50:3,496
WITHIN FEET OF ROWS OF THEM
WIELDING THESE IMPLEMENTS,


1632
1:50:3,496 --> 1:50:8,968
AND YOU CAN'T BUT THINK
THESE ARE THE IMPLEMENTS
THEY USED TO SLAUGHTER


1633
1:50:8,968 --> 1:50:11,404
THEIR VICTIMS
DURING THE GENOCIDE


1634
1:50:11,404 --> 1:50:14,641
BY THE INDIVIDUALLY,
BY THE TENS, BY THE HUNDREDS,


1635
1:50:14,641 --> 1:50:18,811
BY THE THOUSANDS ULTIMATELY.


1636
1:50:18,811 --> 1:50:18,811
OK.


1637
1:50:18,811 --> 1:50:21,147
TELL ME WHEN.


1638
1:50:21,147 --> 1:50:24,284
SHAKING THE HAND OF A KILLER
BEFORE I EVEN KNOW ANYTHING ELSE


1639
1:50:24,284 --> 1:50:26,586
ABOUT HIM EXCEPT
FOR WHAT HIS NAME IS,


1640
1:50:26,586 --> 1:50:28,21
IS A STRANGE THING.


1641
1:50:28,21 --> 1:50:29,489
IT'S AN ACT OF POLITENESS.


1642
1:50:29,489 --> 1:50:32,625
IT'S A TIME
OF HUMAN SHARING,


